name: Indiana

processing_metadata.description: Official Indiana DMV processing rules and validation requirements

global_rules.code_system: Indiana uses code numbers to identify plate types (e.g., 27=Support Our Troops, 30=National Guard, 31=Apportioned, 34=Disabled American Veteran, 35=Disabled, 45=Motorcycle, 46=Passenger, 47=Dealer New, 48=Dealer Used, 49=Veteran Motorcycle, 50=Veteran, 61=Ambulance, 64=Bus, 65=Recreational Vehicle, 67=City Police/Municipal, 68=Municipal Motorcycle, 71=Permanent Trailer, 72=State Motorcycle, 73=State, 77=Semi Tractor, 79=Truck/Trailer 10000 LBS or Less, 88=Purple Heart)
global_rules.character_restrictions: Allows the use of both zero (0) and the letter O. The font is different for the letter O and the number zero 0.; Full rules: Allows the use of both zero (0) and the letter O. The font is different for the letter O and the number zero 0. Tags may have customized registrations that are not standard issue.  **USE INITIAL PASSENGER DROPDOWN**
global_rules.processing_note: Processing rules vary by plate type and are defined in the CSV matrix. Custom processing types will be provided separately.
global_rules.customized_registrations: Tags may have customized registrations that are not standard issue. USE INITIAL PASSENGER DROPDOWN.
global_rules.prefix_suffix_rule: All Indiana license plates have either a prefix or suffix. Prefixes and suffixes can be single, double, or triple alpha (A, AA, AAA) or single, double, or triple numeric (1, 11, 111).
global_rules.zero_vs_o_rule: Indiana allows the use of both number zero (0) and letter O. The font is different for zero vs. letter O.
global_rules.emergency_vehicle_rule: Reject images of Marked Emergency Vehicles for codes 61, 62, 63
global_rules.stacked_characters_rule: For certain plate types, stacked characters or text must be OMITTED (codes 64, 69, 70, 71, 79)
global_rules.include_characters_rule: For RV plates (code 65), the "RV" characters MUST be included/keyed
global_rules.personalized_plates_rule: Codes 42 and 43 are ALWAYS customized/personalized plates
global_rules.weight_class_note: Code 79 is for trucks/trailers with weight class â‰¤10,000 lbs

stacked_characters.position: Y - Stacked characters must be entered as seen.; Y - OMIT BUS when stacked on side of plate. Enter all small characters as seen.; Y - Omit vertical series name on left.
